Prompt engineering is the process of writing clear and detailed instructions to get accurate and useful responses from an AI system

1 Resume Prompt

Weak Prompt
Write a resume for me

Strong Prompt
Create a professional resume for a Computer Science engineering student with skills in Python Machine Learning and Java Include sections for education projects skills and internships Keep it within one page and use clear formatting

Comparison
The weak prompt is very vague and does not give any useful details
The strong prompt clearly mentions the role skills structure and length so the output will be more accurate and organized

2 Business Idea Prompt

Weak Prompt
Give me a business idea

Strong Prompt
Suggest a unique business idea for a college student in India with a low budget under 10000 rupees The idea should be technology based and scalable Also include target audience required resources and expected profit

Comparison
The weak prompt gives no direction so the answer may be generic
The strong prompt provides clear conditions which leads to a practical and useful idea

3 Study Plan Prompt

Weak Prompt
Make a study plan

Strong Prompt
Create a 7 day study plan for a Computer Science student preparing for exams Include 3 to 4 hours of daily study covering Data Structures Aptitude and Python Also include revision time and short breaks

Comparison
The weak prompt lacks details about time subjects and goals
The strong prompt clearly defines duration subjects and structure making the plan more effective

4 Content Writing Prompt

Weak Prompt
Write about AI

Strong Prompt
Write a 200 word explanation of Artificial Intelligence for beginners Use simple language include real life examples and keep the tone engaging

Comparison
The weak prompt is too general and unclear
The strong prompt specifies word limit audience and tone which improves the quality of the content

Key Differences Between Weak and Strong Prompts

Weak prompts are unclear and do not provide enough information
Strong prompts are specific detailed and include clear instructions
Weak prompts lead to generic answers
Strong prompts produce accurate structured and high quality responses

Conclusion
Strong prompts are important because they guide the AI to produce better results By giving clear instructions context and constraints we can improve the quality and usefulness of the output